notes_for_parks_only: iNat: Coast Range and very low elevation Sierra; Taylor: no vouchers in (or very close to) Yosemite; no CCH vouchers; Grindelia camporum / Grindelia nana / Grindelia squarrosa / Grindelia hirsutula (& ~26 more names) collapsed to 1 species (Grindelia hirsutula) by TNRS (and in Flora of North America), but retained as separate by iNat, Jepson. To make matters worse, no actual vouchers in the park, so it is all hearsay if any are in the park, and if so which one. Botti (1980's Yos botanist, who wrote one flora) and Taylor have rather different lists of possible species in the park, with Taylor suggesting Botti misapplications. But FNA basically says 30 taxa collapsed into 1 because ever thought there are regional differences (hence diff species), there are also intermediates everywhere (hence the likely inability to put firm names on the Yosemite-area taxa).
reason_for_parks_list: wrong range-west or south of park at much lower elevations; Coast Range
